org.conqat.lib.commons.serialization.objects

Class SerializedClassValues

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.conqat.lib.commons.serialization.objects.SerializedClassValues

  • public class SerializedClassValues
extends java.lang.Object
    The values of an object corresponding to a single class, i.e. each object has multiple class values, one for each class in its hierarchy. This can store values for all declared (non-transient) fields of a class as well as additional data. The presence of both the fields and the additional data are optional depending on the serialization mechanism used (default Serializable, serializable with custom read/write methods, Externalizable). The old externalization protocol from Java versions before 1.2 is not supported by this class.
